rarchy, and in some cases\n$r$ rounds of our program can be evaluated in time $2^{O(r)}\\poly(n)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Apr 2011 04:58:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-04-26"}
